DOCUMENT();

loadMacros("PG.pl",
           "PGbasicmacros.pl",
#           "PGchoicemacros.pl",
           "PGanswermacros.pl",
#           "PGgraphmacros.pl",
#           "extraAnswerEvaluators.pl",
           "PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl",
#           "parserPopUp.pl"
"MathObjects.pl",
"AnswerFormatHelp.pl",
"PGcourse.pl",
           );

TEXT(beginproblem());

Context("Numeric");

$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a = random(3,17,2);
$d = random(4,10,2);

$b = Compute("2^(1/$d)");
$r = Compute("2^(1/$d) - 1");
$k = Compute("ln($b)");

Context()->texStrings;
BEGIN_TEXT
Give the starting value \(a\), the growth/decay rate \(r\), and
the continuous growth/decay rate \(k\).  If there is exponential
decay your growth rates should negative.
For help entering logarithms, see \{ AnswerFormatHelp("logarithms") \}
$PAR
\( Q = $a \cdot 2^{t/$d} \) has:
$PAR
\( a = \) \{ ans_rule(20) \}
\{ AnswerFormatHelp("numbers") \}
$BR
\( r = \) \{ ans_rule(20) \}
\{ AnswerFormatHelp("numbers") \}
$BR
\( k = \) \{ ans_rule(20) \}
\{ AnswerFormatHelp("numbers") \}
END_TEXT
Context()->normalStrings;

ANS( Real("$a")->cmp() );
ANS( $r->cmp() );
ANS( $k->cmp() );

$r1 = round(10000*$r)/10000;
$k1 = round(10000*$k)/10000;

Context()->texStrings;
SOLUTION(EV3(<<'END_SOLUTION'));
$PAR
$BBOLD  SOLUTION $EBOLD
$PAR
Writing this as \( Q = $a \cdot \left( 2^{1/$d} \right)^t \), we have:
\(a= $a \ \),
\(b=2^{1/$d}\),
\(r = b-1 = 2^{1/$d} - 1\) (about $r1), and
\(k = \ln{b} = \ln(2^{1/$d})\) (about $k1).

END_SOLUTION
Context()->normalStrings;


COMMENT('MathObject version');
ENDDOCUMENT();
